The choice is yours!  Johnnie Walker Black Label is iconic among premium Scotch whiskey. It contains a blend of about 40 whiskies, each of which is aged at least 12 years. Itâ€™s critically acclaimed for its silky delivery, variety of flavors, and smooth finish, and it's very difficult to beat at its price point. Johnnie Walker recommends enjoying it in a rocks glass with ice cubes, but some Black Label enthusiasts would call you crazy for not drinking it neat.  Johnnie Walker Double Black is Johnnie Walker Black Label to the next level. The brand uses hand-picked whiskies that are defined by notes of smoldering charcoal, including more Islay malts, that are chosen for their smoky profile. Then once matured in heavily-charred oak casks, the result is not only a smokier blend, but an unquestionably smooth liquid as well. You can definitely taste the smokiness. Interestingly however, this version is not aged 12 years like it's big brother but is still very smooth. Johnnie Walker Double Black is best enjoyed with water to unlock its complex layers of smouldering spice and smoke.  We've got both at unbeatable prices. Come try some or get some more!
